text: Do Not call this man,my mother made that mistake,she needed a faucet fixed,he charged my mother who is in her 70"s ,$432.50. ,charged her $110.00 for his self $110.00 for the young boy who he said was in training and stood there doing nothing, charged her $85.00 to go get a seal, from Black Rock to Pocahontas ,material and gas$127.00. and the faucet still isn't fixed.WOW...
responseFromOwnerText:
Bless your ❤️ 😢 I’m sorry your unhappy. I replaced a faucet you provided. I do not warranty faucets ( I didn’t provide faucet)a cover plate was needed to turn your 3 handle faucet to a single lever faucet. 
   I charge for two people when two are on site … just because you have never heard of the charging of two service techs……………………. 
   He does what I ask him to. That’s his job. he got the faucet ready for installation. By putting on fittings applying tefelon and pipe dope . Brought in valves to put on for your tub so it could be turned off called isolation valves. Cleaned up and took tools back and fourth to the truck. Cut your water on and off. He is an apprentice plumber. A 4 th year apprentice plumber able to work by himself if I chose to let him.
